Aruba (12Ã¯Â¿Â½30'N, 70Ã¯Â¿Â½W) is located 32 km (19 miles) north of Venezuela and 67 km (42 miles) west of CuraÃ¯Â¿Â½ao, Netherlands Antilles (source: ECNAMP, 1980).
widecast_species.gif (130192 bytes) Click on image to view full figure (128K) Figure 2.
Four species of sea turtle reportedly nest in Aruba: the green turtle or tortuga blanco (Chelonia mydas), the hawksbill or caret (Eretmochelys imbricata), the loggerhead or cawama (Caretta caretta), and the leatherback or driekiel (Dermochelys coriacea).
